Shell script that advances the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant vs. variant structures across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant structures (goals, architecture insights) vs. variant structures (session-specific notes, deferred tasks), and measures classification accuracy against manual labeling.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 10,          # Number of recent pulse logs to analyze\r\n    [double]$Threshold = 0.7      # Minimum frequency for invariance classification\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$RootDir = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir\r\n$LogsDir = Join-Path $RootDir \"logs\"\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 1: Load Pulse Logs ===\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $Lookback pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$LogFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($LogFiles.Count -eq 0) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: No pulse logs found in $LogsDir\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($LogFiles.Count) pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Parse each log into structured sections\r\n$PulseData = @()\r\nforeach ($Log in $LogFiles) {\r\n    $Content = Get-Content $Log.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract section markers\r\n    $Sections = @{\r\n        Filename    = $Log.Name\r\n        Timestamp   = $Log.LastWriteTime\r\n        Goals       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Goals:.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Active      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Active.*?(?=## Pending|$)').Value\r\n        Pending     = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Pending.*?(?=## Notes|$)').Value\r\n        Notes       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Notes.*?(?=## Key|$)').Value\r\n        KeyInsights = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Key Insights.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Observation = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### OBSERVATION.*?(?=### ACTION)').Value\r\n        Action      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### ACTION.*?(?=### MUTATION)').Value\r\n        Mutation    = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### MUTATION.*').Value\r\n    }\r\n    $PulseData += $Sections\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 2: Extract Structural Patterns ===\r\nWrite-Host \"`n=== Phase 2: Pattern Extraction ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n# Count frequency of section types across all pulses\r\n$PatternFreq = @{}\r\nforeach ($Pulse in $PulseData) {\r\n    $Patterns = @($Pulse.Goals, $Pulse.Active, $Pulse.Pending, $Pulse.Notes, $Pulse.KeyInsights)\r\n    foreach ($Pattern in $Patterns) {\r\n        if ($Pattern.Length -gt 10) {\r\n            # Hash pattern for comparison\r\n            $Hash = $Pattern.GetHashCode()\r\n            if ($PatternFreq.ContainsKey($Hash)) {\r\n                $PatternFreq[$Hash].Count++\r\n                $PatternFreq[$Hash].Sample = $Pattern\r\n            } else {\r\n                $PatternFreq[$Hash] = @{ Count = 1; Sample = $Pattern }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 3: Classify Invariant vs Variant ===\r\nWrite-Host\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:00:50"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":690,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 050015\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison, gap-decay mapping, and LLM augmentation\r\n- The big pending item is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nI need to advance the goals. The most concrete pending action is implementing the TIC classifier. Let me look at what files exist that I could work with.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes:\r\n- logs/pulse_*.md files exist\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nThis is a significant implementation task. Let me create a concrete, focused action that advances this goal. I should implement a basic TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads the pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (persistent across sessions) vs variant (session-specific)\r\n3. Measures accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and what structure they have. I'll create a TIC experiment script.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the recent pulse file mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 045915.md`\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Analyzes pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structures (goals, active items, completed items that persist)\r\n3. Identifies variant structures (deferred tasks, flagged items, notes specific to a session)\r\n4. Tests prediction of next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me implement this as a PowerShell script that advances the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant vs. variant structures across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant structures (goals, architecture insights) vs. variant structures (session-specific notes, deferred tasks), and measures classification accuracy against manual labeling.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 10,          # Number of recent pulse logs to analyze\r\n    [double]$Threshold = 0.7      # Minimum frequency for invariance classification\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$RootDir = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir\r\n$LogsDir = Join-Path $RootDir \"logs\"\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 1: Load Pulse Logs ===\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $Lookback pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$LogFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($LogFiles.Count -eq 0) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: No pulse logs found in $LogsDir\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($LogFiles.Count) pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Parse each log into structured sections\r\n$PulseData = @()\r\nforeach ($Log in $LogFiles) {\r\n    $Content = Get-Content $Log.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract section markers\r\n    $Sections = @{\r\n        Filename    = $Log.Name\r\n        Timestamp   = $Log.LastWriteTime\r\n        Goals       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Goals:.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Active      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Active.*?(?=## Pending|$)').Value\r\n        Pending     = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Pending.*?(?=## Notes|$)').Value\r\n        Notes       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Notes.*?(?=## Key|$)').Value\r\n        KeyInsights = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Key Insights.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Observation = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### OBSERVATION.*?(?=### ACTION)').Value\r\n        Action      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### ACTION.*?(?=### MUTATION)').Value\r\n        Mutation    = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### MUTATION.*').Value\r\n    }\r\n    $PulseData += $Sections\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 2: Extract Structural Patterns ===\r\nWrite-Host \"`n=== Phase 2: Pattern Extraction ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n\r\n# Count frequency of section types across all pulses\r\n$PatternFreq = @{}\r\nforeach ($Pulse in $PulseData) {\r\n    $Patterns = @($Pulse.Goals, $Pulse.Active, $Pulse.Pending, $Pulse.Notes, $Pulse.KeyInsights)\r\n    foreach ($Pattern in $Patterns) {\r\n        if ($Pattern.Length -gt 10) {\r\n            # Hash pattern for comparison\r\n            $Hash = $Pattern.GetHashCode()\r\n            if ($PatternFreq.ContainsKey($Hash)) {\r\n                $PatternFreq[$Hash].Count++\r\n                $PatternFreq[$Hash].Sample = $Pattern\r\n            } else {\r\n                $PatternFreq[$Hash] = @{ Count = 1; Sample = $Pattern }\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 3: Classify Invariant vs Variant ===\r\nWrite-Host\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 05:00:50","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343041285}}
