{"type":"message","id":"8bbd35c4","parentId":"c2926985","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:04:20.614Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_436y4roov2sf_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Actually, looking at the recent pulse file mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 045915.md`\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Analyzes pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structures (goals, active items, completed items that persist)\r\n3. Identifies variant structures (deferred tasks, flagged items, notes specific to a session)\r\n4. Tests prediction of next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me implement this as a PowerShell script that advances the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant vs. variant structures across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant structures (goals, architecture insights) vs. variant structures (session-specific notes, deferred tasks), and measures classification accuracy against manual labeling.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 10,          # Number of recent pulse logs to analyze\r\n    [double]$Threshold = 0.7      # Minimum frequency for invariance classification\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$RootDir = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir\r\n$LogsDir = Join-Path $RootDir \"logs\"\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 1: Load Pulse Logs ===\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $Lookback pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$LogFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($LogFiles.Count -eq 0) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: No pulse logs found in $LogsDir\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($LogFiles.Count) pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Parse each log into structured sections\r\n$PulseData = @()\r\nforeach ($Log in $LogFiles) {\r\n    $Content = Get-Content $Log.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract section markers\r\n    $Sections = @{\r\n        Filename    = $Log.Name\r\n        Timestamp   = $Log.LastWriteTime\r\n        Goals       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Goals:.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Active      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Active.*?(?=## Pending|$)').Value\r\n        Pending     = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Pending.*?(?=## Notes|$)').Value\r\n        Notes       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Notes.*?(?=## Key|$)').Value\r\n        KeyInsights = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Key Insights.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Observation = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### OBSERVATION.*?(?=### ACTION)').Value\r\n        Action      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### ACTION.*?(?=### MUTATION)').Value\r\n        Mutation    = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### MUTATION.*').Value\r\n    }\r\n    $PulseData += $Sections\r\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":586,"aggregated":"Actually, looking at the recent pulse file mentioned: `pulse_2026-03-24 045915.md`\r\n\r\nI should create a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Analyzes pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant structures (goals, active items, completed items that persist)\r\n3. Identifies variant structures (deferred tasks, flagged items, notes specific to a session)\r\n4. Tests prediction of next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me implement this as a PowerShell script that advances the TIC experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that can distinguish invariant vs. variant structures across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/tic-classifier.ps1` - a PowerShell script that analyzes pulse logs to identify invariant structures (goals, architecture insights) vs. variant structures (session-specific notes, deferred tasks), and measures classification accuracy against manual labeling.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# 2026-03-24\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 10,          # Number of recent pulse logs to analyze\r\n    [double]$Threshold = 0.7      # Minimum frequency for invariance classification\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"SilentlyContinue\"\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$RootDir = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir\r\n$LogsDir = Join-Path $RootDir \"logs\"\r\n\r\n# === PHASE 1: Load Pulse Logs ===\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Classifier ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading last $Lookback pulse logs...\"\r\n\r\n$LogFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogsDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\n\r\nif ($LogFiles.Count -eq 0) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: No pulse logs found in $LogsDir\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($LogFiles.Count) pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n\r\n# Parse each log into structured sections\r\n$PulseData = @()\r\nforeach ($Log in $LogFiles) {\r\n    $Content = Get-Content $Log.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract section markers\r\n    $Sections = @{\r\n        Filename    = $Log.Name\r\n        Timestamp   = $Log.LastWriteTime\r\n        Goals       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Goals:.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Active      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Active.*?(?=## Pending|$)').Value\r\n        Pending     = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Pending.*?(?=## Notes|$)').Value\r\n        Notes       = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Notes.*?(?=## Key|$)').Value\r\n        KeyInsights = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)## Key Insights.*?(?=##|$)').Value\r\n        Observation = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### OBSERVATION.*?(?=### ACTION)').Value\r\n        Action      = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### ACTION.*?(?=### MUTATION)').Value\r\n        Mutation    = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?s)### MUTATION.*').Value\r\n    }\r\n    $PulseData += $Sections\r\n}","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343060612}}
