{"type":"message","id":"670daee8","parentId":"85d3cd8b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:04:38.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There are multiple pulse logs. The most recent one is `pulse_2026-03-24 050317.md` which was created at 5:03:43 AM - that's just after the current time (5:03 AM). Let me read that one since it was likely generated by the pulse.ps1 script I just ran.\n\nWait, the current time is 5:03 AM. And the most recent log is at 5:03:43 AM, which means the pulse.ps1 script created a new log right after I ran it. Let me read that one.","thinkingSignature":"f9af5d02a845b455408686b6e4fcfab417c72e58dd98946cbfd8bdc53914312b"},{"type":"text","text":"The pulse just ran and created a newer log at 5:03:43 AM. Let me read that one:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ygoy5885fmfv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 050317.md","offset":1,"limit":150}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8264,"output":217,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20435,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774343072652}}
{"type":"message","id":"9f567928","parentId":"670daee8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:04:38.463Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ygoy5885fmfv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 050317\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE (architecture cross-analysis + integration spec)\r\n2. Key completed work: Architecture comparison, Gap-Decay synthesis, LLM-Augmented pulse setup\r\n3. Pending: PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI, significance scoring, λ tuning, wiring to TemporalAttention backend, compression ratio measurement\r\n4. NEW Priority: TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression) - this is the next action to advance Phase 1\r\n\r\nThe \"NEXT ACTION\" clearly states:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThis is the most concrete next step. I should implement a TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLooking at the notes:\r\n- Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-24 050015.md\r\n- Breakaway is stateless, gaps = compression\r\n- Session gaps are temporal hashing\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Read the pulse logs to understand their structure\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Test on the pulse logs\r\n4. Measure accuracy against success criteria\r\n\r\nSince this is a single concrete action, I should start by creating the TIC experiment code. Let me first check what pulse logs exist and their structure, then implement a simple TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check the logs directory and create the TIC classifier experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to advance Phase 1. The pulse logs in `logs/` directory are the testbed, but I need to first examine their structure to implement the classifier effectively.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier experiment script that will analyze pulse logs, identify invariant vs variant content, and measure classification accuracy against the >70% success criterion.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\nPhase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n\r\nHypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\nCompressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\nSuccess Criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6}\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs():\r\n    \"\"\"Load all pulse log files sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = []\r\n    for f in sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n        logs.append(f.read_text())\r\n    return logs\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_blocks(log):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content blocks from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    blocks = {}\r\n    sections = [\"OBSERVATION\", \"ACTION\", \"MUTATION\", \"PENDING\", \"NOTES\"]\r\n    for section in sections:\r\n        match = re.search(rf\"### {section}\\n(.+?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", log, re.DOTALL)\r\n        if match:\r\n            blocks[section] = match.group(1).strip()\r\n    return blocks\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(logs):\r\n    \"\"\"Identify content that repeats across multiple pulses (invariants).\"\"\"\r\n    content_freq = Counter()\r\n    all_contents = []\r\n    \r\n    for log in logs:\r\n        blocks = extract_content_blocks(log)\r\n        content = str(blocks)\r\n        content_freq[content] += 1\r\n        all_contents.append((log, content))\r\n    \r\n    # Content appearing in >50% of pulses is invariant\r\n    threshold = len(logs) * 0.5\r\n    invariants = {c for c, freq in content_freq.items() if freq > threshold}\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant_variant(log, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a pulse log as invariant or variant dominant.\"\"\"\r\n    blocks = extract_content_blocks(log)\r\n    content = str(blocks)\r\n    \r\n    if content in invariants:\r\n        return \"invariant\"\r\n    return \"variant\"\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(current_log, next_log, invariants):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict if next pulse will share invariants with current.\"\"\"\r\n    current_class = classify_invariant_variant(current_log, invariants)\r\n    next_class = classify_invariant_variant(next_log, invariants)\r\n    return current_class == next_class\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=== TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment ===\\n\")\r\n    \r\n    logs = load_pulse_logs()\r\n    print(f\"Loaded {len(logs)} pulse logs\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(logs) < 5:\r\n        print(\"Insufficient logs for experiment (need at least 5)\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 1: Identify invariants\r\n    invariants = extract_invariants(logs)\r\n    print(f\"Found {len(invariants)} invariant content patterns\")\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 2: Classify each pulse\r\n    classifications = []\r\n    for i, log in enumerate(logs):\r\n        pred_class = classify_invariant_variant(log, invariants)\r\n        classifications.append(pred_class)\r\n    \r\n    inv_count = sum(1 for c in classifications if c == \"invariant\")\r\n    var_count = sum(1 for c in classifications if c == \"variant\")\r\n    print(f\"Classification: {inv_count} invariant, {var_count} variant\")\r\n    \r\n    # Phase 3: Next-pulse prediction\r\n    correct_predictions = 0\r\n    for i in range(len(logs) - 1):\r\n        if predict_next_p\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n\n[3 more lines in file. Use offset=151 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343078461}}
