{"type":"message","id":"9c4a71c0","parentId":"3fd37c21","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:05:04.527Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_c875qhubrm1l_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 045915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. The session has established a foundation with Breakaway architecture\r\n2. Key insights have been synthesized about compression-causal duality\r\n3. The next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n4. I need to implement this classifier to test the hypothesis about invariant/variant classification\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the pulse logs and what tools/data are available to implement the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nFirst, I should observe the current state of the logs directory to understand what pulse logs exist.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires implementing a classifier on existing pulse logs. The hypothesis is that causal structure equals invariant structure - compressors that find invariants have discovered causation. I need to implement this on the `logs/pulse_*.md` files to test invariant/variant classification.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for temporal invariants. This script will:\r\n1. Load recent pulse logs (last 20)\r\n2. Extract features from each pulse\r\n3. Classify content as invariant (persisting across pulses) vs variant (changing)\r\n4. Attempt next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n5. Output accuracy metrics for both classification and prediction\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant accuracy, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$Lookback = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n\r\n# --- Feature Extraction ---\r\nfunction Extract-Features {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    \r\n    $features = @{\r\n        lines = ($Content -split \"`n\").Count\r\n        words = ($Content -split \"\\s+\").Count\r\n        hasGoal = $Content -match \"## (Active|Pending|Completed)\"\r\n        hasMutation = $Content -match \"### MUTATION\"\r\n        hasObservation = $Content -match \"### OBSERVATION\"\r\n        hasAction = $Content -match \"### ACTION\"\r\n        pulseNum = if ($Content -match \"pulse_(\\d+)\") { [int]$matches[1] } else { 0 }\r\n        phaseComplete = ($Content -match \"COMPLETE|✅\") \r\n        hasHypothesis = $Content -match \"Hypothesis|hypothesis|insight|Insight\"\r\n    }\r\n    return $features\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Invariant Detection ---\r\nfunction Test-Invariant {\r\n    param($Features1, $Features2, $Threshold = 0.8)\r\n    \r\n    $matchCount = 0\r\n    $totalChecks = 4\r\n    \r\n    if ($Features1.hasGoal -eq $Features2.hasGoal) { $matchCount++ }\r\n    if ($Features1.hasMutation -eq $Features2.hasMutation) { $matchCount++ }\r\n    if ($Features1.hasAction -eq $Features2.hasAction) { $matchCount++ }\r\n    if ($Features1.hasHypothesis -eq $Features2.hasHypothesis) { $matchCount++ }\r\n    \r\n    return ($matchCount / $totalChecks) -ge $Threshold\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Main TIC Experiment ---\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"Lookback: $Lookback pulses`n\"\r\n\r\n# Load pulse logs\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $Lookback\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"Insufficient pulse logs (need at least 5, found $($pulseFiles.Count))\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Loaded $($pulseFiles.Count) pulse logs`n\"\r\n\r\n# Extract features\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $features = Extract-Features -Content $content\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Features = $features\r\n        Content = $content\r\n\n[44 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774343104526}}
